        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-01-28 00:02:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJames, any patches you have can be pushed and landed independently of this one.  It is unlikely that your patches would have any conflicts with this, so long as they don't change test_51b() and test_51ba().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fe4cdc94da49e3e1f932f302f2f8222e5347c156",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2014-01-28 00:06:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis patch fixes the problem that we are currently experiencing with filling an MDT. If test_51b is run alone without running test_51ab, we run into the same problem. We don't run our testing this way, but nothing in the tests prohibit people from running test_51b alone.\n\nDo you think test_51b should clean up after itself or that the two tests should be combined?\n\nI still think this patch is fine, but it seems like we have not totally fixed this problem.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
