    {
      "id": "1ce0e176c3967a0fa0defb710a2f65beeeeb4bc0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-01-28 07:37:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJames, I think in many testing environments the extra subdirectories created in test_51b would not create a huge problem if they are not cleaned up until the end of the test.  They will all be deleted at the end of sanity.sh even if test_51ba is not run.  If test_51ba is run without test_51b it will detect this and skip the test.\n\nI agree it could be improved further, but I'd prefer to spend time fixing the many other areas that also need to be improved.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
